<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>ACIC Data Challenge Process Flowchart</h1>
        <div class="flowchart">
            <div class="stage">
                <div class="stage-number">1</div>
                <div class="stage-content">
                    <div class="stage-title">DATA GENERATION & SIMULATION</div>
                    <div class="stage-description">
                        Organizers (Mathematica team) create thousands of synthetic datasets based on real-world patterns
                    </div>
                    <ul class="details-list">
                        <li>Use <span class="highlight">real healthcare/education data structures</span> as templates</li>
                        <li>Embed <span class="highlight">known true causal effects</span> (ground truth)</li>
                        <li>Include realistic challenges: <span class="highlight">confounding</span>, <span class="highlight">selection bias</span>, <span class="highlight">heterogeneous effects</span></li>
                        <li>Create hierarchical structures (e.g., patients nested in practices)</li>
                        <li>Include highly skewed outcomes (e.g., Medicare spending)</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="arrow"></div>
            
            <div class="stage">
                <div class="stage-number">2</div>
                <div class="stage-content">
                    <div class="stage-title">DATA RELEASE</div>
                    <div class="stage-description">
                        Simulated datasets are released to participating teams
                    </div>
                    <ul class="details-list">
                        <li>Teams receive <span class="highlight">covariate data</span> (X)</li>
                        <li>Teams receive <span class="highlight">treatment indicators</span> (T)</li>
                        <li>Teams receive <span class="highlight">observed outcomes</span> (Y)</li>
                        <li><span class="highlight">True causal effects remain hidden</span> from participants</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="arrow"></div>
            
            <div class="stage">
                <div class="stage-number">3</div>
                <div class="stage-content">
                    <div class="stage-title">COMPETING ALGORITHMS APPLY METHODS</div>
                    <div class="stage-description">
                        Teams apply their causal inference methods to estimate treatment effects
                    </div>
                    <ul class="details-list">
                        <li><span class="highlight">Machine Learning approaches</span> (Random Forests, Neural Networks)</li>
                        <li><span class="highlight">Bayesian methods</span> (BART, Gaussian Processes)</li>
                        <li><span class="highlight">Propensity score methods</span> (Matching, Weighting, Stratification)</li>
                        <li><span class="highlight">Doubly robust estimators</span> (AIPW, TMLE)</li>
                        <li><span class="highlight">Ensemble methods</span> combining multiple approaches</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="arrow"></div>
            
            <div class="stage">
                <div class="stage-number">4</div>
                <div class="stage-content">
                    <div class="stage-title">TEAMS SUBMIT ESTIMATES</div>
                    <div class="stage-description">
                        Participating teams submit their causal effect estimates
                    </div>
                    <ul class="details-list">
                        <li>Estimates of <span class="highlight">Average Treatment Effect (ATE)</span></li>
                        <li>Estimates of <span class="highlight">Conditional Average Treatment Effects (CATE)</span></li>
                        <li>Uncertainty quantification (<span class="highlight">confidence/credible intervals</span>)</li>
                        <li>Subgroup effect estimates</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="arrow"></div>
            
            <div class="stage">
                <div class="stage-number">5</div>
                <div class="stage-content">
                    <div class="stage-title">EVALUATION METRICS</div>
                    <div class="stage-description">
                        Organizers compare submitted estimates against known ground truth
                    </div>
                    <ul class="details-list">
                        <li><span class="highlight">Bias</span>: How close are estimates to true effects?</li>
                        <li><span class="highlight">Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE)</span>: Overall accuracy</li>
                        <li><span class="highlight">Coverage</span>: Do confidence intervals contain true values?</li>
                        <li><span class="highlight">Precision</span>: Width of confidence intervals</li>
                        <li><span class="highlight">Heterogeneity capture</span>: How well do methods identify effect variation?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="arrow"></div>
            
            <div class="stage">
                <div class="stage-number">6</div>
                <div class="stage-content">
                    <div class="stage-title">RESULTS & INSIGHTS</div>
                    <div class="stage-description">
                        Winners announced and lessons learned shared with the field
                    </div>
                    <ul class="details-list">
                        <li>Identify <span class="highlight">best-performing methods</span> for different scenarios</li>
                        <li>Reveal <span class="highlight">strengths and weaknesses</span> of various approaches</li>
                        <li>Inform <span class="highlight">future policy evaluations</span></li>
                        <li>Advance the field of <span class="highlight">causal inference methodology</span></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>